spanishExample: ¡No se preocupe! Nos importa.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Don’t worry! We care about it.

spanishExample: ¡No se preocupen! Ese no era un recuerdo importante.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Don’t worry! That wasn’t an important memory.

spanishExample: ¿Te vas a preocupar por eso?
englishTranslation: Are you going to get worried about that?

spanishExample: De veras, creo que le gustará esta palabra.
englishTranslation: Really, I think she’ll like this word.

spanishExample: De veras, no le gustó eso para nada.
englishTranslation: Really, she didn’t like that at all.

spanishExample: De veras, tienes que hacer de cuenta que no te preocupa.
englishTranslation: Really, you have to pretend it doesn’t worry you.

spanishExample: En primer lugar, creo que le ha gustado.
englishTranslation: In the first place, I think she has liked it.

spanishExample: En primer lugar, no te preocupes, ya tengo seis.
englishTranslation: In the first place, don’t worry about it, I already have six.

spanishExample: Ese es su mejor recuerdo porque es seguro de sí mismo.
englishTranslation: That’s his best memory because he is sure of himself.

spanishExample: Espero que le guste para que le importe.
englishTranslation: I hope she likes it so that she cares about it.

spanishExample: Le gustaba cuando tenía cinco de esos.
englishTranslation: She used to like it when she had five of those.

spanishExample: Le gustaría estar aquí a las siete en punto.
englishTranslation: She would like to be here at seven o’clock.

spanishExample: Le importaría si tuviera cinco cuentas.
englishTranslation: I would matter to him if I had five accounts.

spanishExample: Me gustaban esos lugares donde hablaban entre sí.
englishTranslation: I used to like those places where they talked among themselves.

spanishExample: Me importaría si hicieras eso.
englishTranslation: It would matter to me if you did that.

spanishExample: Me preocupo cuando lo que dices no tiene sentido.
englishTranslation: I get worried when what you say doesn’t make sense.

spanishExample: Me preocupo por tener cuatro cuentas.
englishTranslation: I’m worried about having four accounts.

spanishExample: Mis amigos se han preocupado y no me gusta.
englishTranslation: My friends have worried and I don’t like it.

spanishExample: No le gustaba antes porque creía que era mi culpa.
englishTranslation: She didn’t like me before because she thought it was my fault.

spanishExample: No le gusto, pero me da igual.
englishTranslation: He doesn’t like me, but it’s all the same to me.

spanishExample: No le importaban las cosas que te gustan.
englishTranslation: She didn’t care about the things you like.

spanishExample: No le importará si no tiene sentido.
englishTranslation: It won’t matter to her if it doesn’t make sense.

spanishExample: Puede ser que estemos ahí a las cuatro en punto.
englishTranslation: It might be that we’re there at four o’clock.

spanishExample: Puede ser que tenga siete ahora, pero me da igual.
englishTranslation: It might be that she has seven now, but it’s all the same to me.

spanishExample: Sí, pueden hablar entre sí, me gustaría.
englishTranslation: Yes, they can talk among themselves, I would like it.

spanishExample: Te preocupas cuando no tienes un plan.
englishTranslation: You worry when you don’t have a plan.

spanishExample: Tiene que darse cuenta de que seis no me preocupan.
englishTranslation: She has to realize that six don’t worry me.

spanishExample: Tiene que hacer de cuenta que es segura de sí misma.
englishTranslation: She has to pretend that she is sure of herself.
